{"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewDimensions"},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/s8CopyableP","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/SQ"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"A view’s size and alignment guides in its own coordinate space.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI"]]},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Getting-dimensions","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewDimensions\/height","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewDimensions\/width"],"title":"Getting dimensions"},{"anchor":"Subscripts","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewDimensions\/subscript(_:)","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewDimensions\/subscript(explicit:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Subscripts"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Aligning-views","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HorizontalAlignment","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VerticalAlignment","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AlignmentID"],"generated":true,"title":"Aligning views"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore14ViewDimensionsV","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ViewDimensions","kind":"identifier"}],"remoteSource":{"fileName":"ViewDimensions.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Layout\/View\/ViewDimensions.swift#L95"},"symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ViewDimensions","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ViewDimensions","roleHeading":"Structure"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/viewdimensions"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ViewDimensions","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This structure contains the size and alignment guides of a view.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You receive an instance of this structure to use in a variety of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"layout calculations, like when you:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Define a default value for a custom alignment guide;"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"see "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AlignmentID\/defaultValue(in:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Modify an alignment guide on a view;"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"see "},{"code":"View\/alignmentGuide(_:computeValue:)-9mdoh","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Ask for the dimensions of a subview of a custom view layout;","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LayoutSubview\/dimensions(in:)","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"text":"Custom alignment guides","anchor":"Custom-alignment-guides","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You receive an instance of this structure as the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AlignmentID\/defaultValue(in:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method that you implement to produce"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the default offset for an alignment guide, or as the first argument to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"closure you provide to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/alignmentGuide(_:computeValue:)-6y3u2"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view modifier to override the default calculation for an alignment guide."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In both cases you can use the instance, if helpful, to calculate the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"offset for the guide. For example, you could compute a default offset"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for a custom "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VerticalAlignment","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a fraction of the view’s "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewDimensions\/height","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["private struct FirstThirdAlignment: AlignmentID {","    static func defaultValue(in context: ViewDimensions) -> CGFloat {","        context.height \/ 3","    }","}","","extension VerticalAlignment {","    static let firstThird = VerticalAlignment(FirstThirdAlignment.self)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As another example, you could use the view dimensions instance to look"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"up the offset of an existing guide and modify it:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct ViewDimensionsOffset: View {","    var body: some View {","        VStack(alignment: .leading) {","            Text(\"Default\")","            Text(\"Indented\")","                .alignmentGuide(.leading) { context in","                    context[.leading] - 10","                }","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example above indents the second text view because the subtraction"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"moves the second text view’s leading guide in the negative x direction,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Openwhich is to the left in the view’s coordinate space. As a result,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI moves the second text view to the right, relative to the first"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text view, to keep their leading guides aligned:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Layout direction","anchor":"Layout-direction","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The discussion above describes a left-to-right language environment,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but you don’t change your guide calculation to operate in a right-to-left"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"environment. OpenSwiftUI moves the view’s origin from the left to the right side"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the view and inverts the positive x direction. As a result,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the existing calculation produces the same effect, but in the opposite"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"direction."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can see this if you use the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/environment(_:_:)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modifier to set the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/EnvironmentValues\/layoutDirection"},{"text":" property for the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view that you defined above:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["ViewDimensionsOffset()","    .environment(\\.layoutDirection, .rightToLeft)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With no change in your guide, this produces the desired effect —","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it indents the second text view’s right side, relative to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"first text view’s right side. The leading edge is now on the right,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and the direction of the offset is reversed:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ViewDimensions/width":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The view’s width."}],"title":"width","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/viewdimensions\/width","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"width","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGFloat","preciseIdentifier":"s:14CoreFoundation7CGFloatV","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewDimensions\/width","type":"topic"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ViewDimensions/subscript(_:)":{"title":"subscript(_:)","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/viewdimensions\/subscript(_:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"subscript"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"text":":)","kind":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Gets the value of the given horizontal guide."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewDimensions\/subscript(_:)"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ViewDimensions/height":{"